race.comment: Decimated by the scratchings. MINI ANGEL (10) gets chance to bounce back. Maiden winner two back then below expectations last time on top of the ground. Freshened, back to 1200m and chances enhances with the softer footing. Looks ideally placed to return to winning form. ZAMORA (16) was a maiden winner two back then ran well below best latest. Placed this trip three back and with good early pace can give a sight.  TIPSY GYPSY (9) is a lightly raced mare progressing well. Broke her maiden status last start by a long neck over 1200m at this track. Shows promise and has Rawiller and a low draw. Could be over the odds.  SOOBOOMA (15) doesn't win out of turn but will find this easier and on best figures can sneak into the finish.
